{{Infobox Journal | title = Public Archaeology | cover = Public Archaeology cover.jpg | editor = [[Tim Schadla-Hall]] | discipline = [[Archaeology]], [[Cultural heritage management]] | abbreviation = Public Archaeol. | publisher = [[Maney Publishing]] | country = United Kingdom | frequency = Quarterly | history = 2000-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.maney.co.uk/search?fwaction=show&fwid=709 | link1 = http://www.ingentaconnect.com/content/maney/pua | link1-name = Online access | link2 = | link2-name = | RSS = | atom = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 45034765 | LCCN = 00227110 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1465-5187 | eISSN = 1753-5530 }} '''''Public Archaeology''''' is a quarterly [[peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] established in 2000, edited by [[Tim Schadla-Hall]] and published by [[Maney Publishing]]. It covers the relationships between practical [[archaeology]], [[archaeological theory]] and [[cultural heritage]] management models, and the involvement of wider civic, governmental, and community concerns.
